%3AJihad" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-:0-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-:0_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-:0_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFRoy_Jackson2014" class="citation book cs1">Roy Jackson (2014). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=5XPMAgAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PA173"><i>What is Islamic philosophy?</i></a>. Routledge. p.&#160;173. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1317814047" title="Special:BookSources/978-1317814047"><bdi>978-1317814047</bdi></a>. <q><i>jihad</i> Literally 'struggle' which has many meanings, though most frequently associated with war.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=What+is+Islamic+philosophy%3F&amp;rft.pages=173&amp;rft.pub=Routledge&amp;rft.date=2014&amp;rft.isbn=978-1317814047&amp;rft.au=Roy+Jackson&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D5XPMAgAAQBAJ%26pg%3DPA173&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJihad" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
