<li id="cite_note-onlinelibrary.wiley.com-125"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-onlinelibrary.wiley.com_125-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFAl-Dawoody2013" class="citation journal cs1">Al-Dawoody, Ahmed (27 August 2013). "Armed Jihad in the Islamic Legal Tradition". <i>Religion Compass</i>. <b>7</b> (11): 476–484. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1111%2Frec3.12071">10.1111/rec3.12071</a>. <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:143395594">143395594</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Religion+Compass&amp;rft.atitle=Armed+Jihad+in+the+Islamic+Legal+Tradition&amp;rft.volume=7&amp;rft.issue=11&amp;rft.pages=476-484&amp;rft.date=2013-08-27&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1111%2Frec3.12071&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A143395594%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft.aulast=Al-Dawoody&amp;rft.aufirst=Ahmed&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJihad" class="Z3988"></span></span>
